cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.DM, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a novel framework for dynamic ensemble selection using meta-learning. The paper focuses on machine learning techniques and proposes a new approach for selecting the best classifier for a given input instance. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the use of meta-features and meta-classifiers, which are common techniques in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also mentions the use of different criteria to measure the level of competence of a classifier, which is related to data mining (cs.DM). Finally, the paper discusses the use of different training scenarios, which is related to neural networks (cs.NE).
